main event: A strange native copper object was brought to the attention of the US Air Force, but no identification could be established.
interesting points: The object was described as a 'strange native copper cover' or 'opened up copper covering'.
The presence of native copper in the area was noted as being closely tied to the history of the region.
The Air Force consultant, J. Allen Hynek, responded to the person who submitted the object, indicating it was a 'good conversation piece'.
There were references to some UFO information in a magazine that the person wanted to share, but no further details were provided.
The Chicago Tribune provided a response indicating they could not provide any further information on government sightings, as those were handled by a different office.
